			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Aria of Asceticism quest walkthrough<a name="14935"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 9 04 3:22 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I did this solo also but a little different, I invised in to the tavern, pulled the Tavern wench (take note of where she stands because you'll want to know it for later) with a burst of chant and quick hit invis before she got to me....then ran outside (still had SAC up so I was fast) and pulled her to near the zone.  Chantted her down quickly then went back in.  I invised into the tavern again and targeted the troubador...I then stood just infront of where the tavern wench spawns.  Basically as close to the door as you can and still have a line of site on the troubardor...nothing should agro if you dont go past the end of the counter on the left.
<br />

<br />
Once you start singing the song and before it hits, back up into the spot where the wench spawns.  Since the server calculates LOS at the begining of our singing it doesn't matter that you are no longer directly in line with teh troubador, and you are now in a position that the other two in the center (right in front of the hole in the floor) wont agro.
<br />

<br />
As soon as my chant hits the troubador, I click over to invis and run him to a clear spot to chant him down (either a camped ship or near the zone into gunthak.  Because you are invis and the way faction works in dulak you dont get social agro with the tavern spawns if you are invis.  You will get a single pull everytime.
<br />

<br />
I did this routine 3 times and got my drop.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
